# ðŸ“Œ **2. After-Sales / Field Service Engineer â€” Example from Medical Equipment OEM**

**Job Title:** After-Sales / Field Service Engineer
**Location:** [City / Region]

### **Job Overview**

The After-Sales Engineer supports customer satisfaction and product uptime by providing *remote and on-site* technical support, installation services, training, and preventive maintenance on medical equipment. ([Glints][3])

### **Key Responsibilities**

* Deliver remote and on-site technical support to diagnose and repair hardware/software issues. ([Glints][3])
* Lead installation, calibration, and operational qualification (OQ) of medical devices. ([Glints][3])
* Conduct training sessions for clinicians and engineers on system operation. ([Glints][3])
* Record and analyze repair activities; provide feedback to product and R&D teams. ([Glints][3])
* Perform preventive maintenance to reduce downtime and ensure compliance. ([Glints][3])
* Support pre-sales and coordination with the sales team as needed. ([Glints][3])
* Complete additional tasks as assigned by supervisors. ([Glints][3])

### **Qualifications**

* Associate or Bachelorâ€™s degree in Electronics, Mechanical, or related engineering field. ([Glints][3])
* 3+ yearsâ€™ experience in field service or after-sales roles, preferably in medical devices. ([Glints][3])
* Strong problem-solving and communication skills. ([Glints][3])
* Good business English communication; multilingual skills preferred. ([Glints][3])

